properties.name: BathroomsFull
properties.description: A room containing all four of the four elements constituting a bath: toilet, sink, bathtub, shower head (in tub or stall). Some may considered a sink, toilet and tub (without a shower) a full bath, while others may consider that to be a three-quarters bath. In the event that the BathroomsThreeQuarter field is not in use, this field may represent the sum of all full and three-quarters bathrooms.

properties.name: BathroomsHalf
properties.description: A room containing two of the four elements constituting a bath: toilet, sink, bathtub, shower head (in a tub or stall). A half bath will typically contain a sink and toilet.

properties.name: BathroomsOneQuarter
properties.description: A room containing one of the four elements constituting a bath: toilet, sink, bathtub, shower head (in tub or stall). Examples include a vanity with a sink or a water closet (WC), which is a room with only a toilet.

properties.name: BathroomsPartial
properties.description: The number of partial bathrooms in the property being sold/leased. When used in combination with the BathroomsFull field, this replaces (or is the sum of) all half and one-quarter bathrooms. In the event that the BathroomsThreeQuarter field is not used, BathroomsFull replaces (or is the sum of) all full and three-quarters baths. This field should not be used in combination with the BathroomsOneQuarter or BathroomsHalf fields.

properties.name: BathroomsThreeQuarter
properties.description: A room containing three of the four elements constituting a bath: toilet, sink, bathtub, shower head (in a tub or stall). A typical three-quarters bath will contain a sink, toilet and shower. Some may considered a sink, toilet and tub (without a shower) a three-quarters bath, while others consider this to be a full bath.

properties.name: BathroomsTotalInteger
properties.description: The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example, for a property with two full bathrooms and one half bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer would be 3. Expressing this example as 2.5 would require a non-standard field name. Decimal-based bathrooms are not recommended, they are possible via the Data Dictionary's extensibility.

properties.name: BedroomsPossible
properties.description: The sum of BedroomsTotal plus other rooms that may be used as a bedroom but are not defined as a bedroom per local policy.

properties.name: Make
properties.description: The make of the mobile or manufactured home.

properties.name: ManagerExpense
properties.description: The annual expense that is not paid directly by the tenant and is included in the Operating Expense calculations. This is for an individual manager. Use ProfessionalManagementExpense for a management company.

properties.name: MapCoordinate
properties.description: A map coordinate for the property, as determined by local custom. This is not necessarily the same as the geographic coordinate but may depend on the coordinate system used by whatever mapping service is customarily used by the listing service.

properties.name: MapCoordinateSource
properties.description: The name of the map or map book publisher.

properties.name: MapURL
properties.description: A Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) to a map of the property.

properties.name: Media
properties.description: A collection of media items related to the Property record.

properties.name: MiddleOrJuniorSchool
properties.description: The name of the junior or middle school having a catchment area that includes the associated property.

properties.name: MiddleOrJuniorSchoolDistrict
properties.description: The name of the junior or middle school district having a catchment area that includes the associated property.
properties.displayNameEs: Distrito de Escuela Media o Intermedia

properties.name: MLSAreaMajor
properties.description: The major marketing area name, as defined by the MLS or other nongovernmental organization. If there is only one MLS area in use, it must be the MLSAreaMajor.

properties.name: MLSAreaMinor
properties.description: The minor/submarketing area name, as defined by the MLS or other nongovernmental organization. If there is only one MLS area in use, it must be the MLSAreaMajor.

properties.name: MlsStatus
properties.description: A local or regional status that is well known by business users. Each MlsStatus field must map to a single StandardStatus. Multiple MlsStatus fields may map to a single StandardStatus.

properties.name: MobileDimUnits
properties.description: A pick list of the unit of linear measurement (e.g., Feet, Meters, Yards, Kilometers, Miles).

properties.name: MobileHomeRemainsYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not the mobile home is to remain and be included in the sale of the property.

properties.name: MobileLength
properties.description: The length of the mobile/manufactured home.

properties.name: MobileWidth
properties.description: The width of the mobile/manufactured home.

properties.name: Model
properties.description: The model of the mobile or manufactured home.

properties.name: ModificationTimestamp
properties.description: The transactional timestamp automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the date/time the listing was last modified.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date de la modification

properties.name: NetOperatingIncome
properties.description: The net operating income is the revenue from a property after operating expenses have been deducted but before deducting income taxes and financing expenses (interest and principal payments). For example, gross income - operating expenses = net operating income (NOI).

properties.name: NewConstructionYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not the property is newly constructed and has not been previously occupied.

properties.name: NewTaxesExpense
properties.description: The annual expense that is not paid directly by the tenant and is included in the Operating Expense calculations.

properties.name: NumberOfBuildings
properties.description: The total number of separate buildings included in the income property.

properties.name: NumberOfFullTimeEmployees
properties.description: The current number of individuals employed by the business on a full-time basis.

properties.name: NumberOfLots
properties.description: The total number of lots on the property or included in the sale. Land properties are often sold with multiple lots. It is important to be able to describe how many lots are in the property, and not all lots have separate parcel IDs.

properties.name: NumberOfPads
properties.description: The number of pads or spaces in the mobile home park.

properties.name: NumberOfPartTimeEmployees
properties.description: The current number of individuals employed by the business on a part-time basis.

properties.name: NumberOfSeparateElectricMeters
properties.description: The total number of separate electric meters on the property.

properties.name: NumberOfSeparateGasMeters
properties.description: The total number of separate gas meters on the property.
properties.displayNameFr: Nombre de compteurs de gaz séparés
properties.displayNameEs: Número de Medidores de Gas Individuales

properties.name: NumberOfSeparateWaterMeters
properties.description: The total number of separate water meters on the property.
properties.displayNameEs: Número de Medidores de Agua Individuales

properties.name: NumberOfUnitsInCommunity
properties.description: The total number of units in the building, complex or community. This is not the number of units being sold, but rather the size of the community in which the dwelling being sold is located.

properties.name: NumberOfUnitsLeased
properties.description: The total number of units currently under a lease agreement.
properties.displayNameFr: Nombre d’unités sous contrat de location

properties.name: NumberOfUnitsMoMo
properties.displayName: Number Of Units Month To Month
properties.description: The total number of units leasable month to month.
properties.displayNameFr: Nombre d’unités pouvant être louées au mois

properties.name: NumberOfUnitsTotal
properties.description: Total number of units included in the income property, occupied or unoccupied.

properties.name: NumberOfUnitsVacant
properties.description: The number of units currently vacant.

properties.name: OccupantName
properties.description: The name of the current occupant, if any, of the property being sold.

properties.name: OccupantPhone
properties.description: North American 10-digit phone numbers should be in the format of ###-###-#### (separated by hyphens). Other conventions should use the common local standard. International numbers should be preceded by a plus symbol.

properties.name: OccupantType
properties.description: A field that describes the type of occupant (i.e., Owner, Tenant, Vacant).

properties.name: OffMarketDate
properties.description: The date the listing was taken off market. Where possible, this date represents the date entered by the agent, reflecting when the change occurred contractually, not a timestamp of when the change was made in the MLS.

properties.name: OffMarketTimestamp
properties.description: The transactional timestamp automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the most recent date/time the listing's status was set to an off-market status (not Active or Backup)
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date du retrait du marché
properties.displayNameEs: Marca de Tiempo Fuera del Mercado

properties.name: OnMarketDate
properties.description: The date the listing was placed on market. Where possible, this date is reflective of the date entered by the agent reflecting when the change occurred contractually, not a timestamp of when the change was made in the MLS.
properties.displayNameFr: Date de l’entrée sur le marché

properties.name: OnMarketTimestamp
properties.description: The transactional timestamp automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the most recent date/time the listing's status was set to Active or Backup. This also includes initial input of the listing to Active/Backup or from a draft or approval status to Active/Backup.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date de l’entrée sur le marché
properties.displayNameEs: Marca de Tiempo Lanzamiento al Mercado

properties.name: OpenHouse
properties.description: A collection of open house items related to the Property record.

properties.name: OpenHouseModificationTimestamp
properties.description: A system-generated timestamp of when the last update or change to the open house information for this listing was made.

properties.name: OpenParkingSpaces
properties.description: The number of open or uncovered parking spaces included in the sale.

properties.name: OpenParkingYN
properties.description: A flag indicating that any parking spaces associated with the property are not covered by a roof.

properties.name: OperatingExpense
properties.description: The costs associated with the operation and maintenance of an income-producing property.

properties.name: OperatingExpenseIncludes
properties.description: When individual expense fields are not used and only a total is entered, this lists the expenses that are included in the OperatingExpense field.

properties.name: OriginalEntryTimestamp
properties.description: The transactional timestamp automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the date/time the listing was entered and made visible to members of the MLS.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date de l’entrée originale

properties.name: OriginalListPrice
properties.description: The original price of the property on the initial agreement between the seller and the seller's broker.

properties.name: OriginatingSystem
properties.description: The originating system of the Property record.

properties.name: OriginatingSystemID
properties.description: The OUID Resource's OrganizationUniqueId of the originating record provider. The originating system is the system with authoritative control over the record (e.g., the MLS where the listing was input). In cases where the originating system was not where the record originated (the authoritative system), see the Originating System fields.

properties.name: OriginatingSystemKey
properties.description: The system key, a unique record identifier, from the originating system. The originating system is the system with authoritative control over the record (e.g., the MLS where the listing was input). There may be cases where the source system (how the record was received) is not the originating system. See Source System Key for more information.

properties.name: OriginatingSystemName
properties.description: The name of the originating record provider, most commonly the name of the MLS. The place where the listing is originally input by the member. The legal name of the company.

properties.name: OtherEquipment
properties.description: A list of other equipment that will be included in the sale of the property.

properties.name: OtherExpense
properties.description: The annual expense that is not paid directly by the tenant and is included in the Operating Expense calculations.

properties.name: OtherParking
properties.description: Other types of parking available to, or part of, the property.

properties.name: OtherStructures
properties.description: A list of structures other than the main dwelling (e.g., Guest House, Barn, Shed).

properties.name: OwnerName
properties.description: The name of the owner of the property being sold.

properties.name: OwnerPays
properties.description: A list of expenses for the property paid for by the owner as opposed to the tenant (e.g., Water, Trash, Electric).

properties.name: OwnerPhone
properties.description: North American 10-digit phone numbers should be in the format of ###-###-#### (separated by hyphens). Other conventions should use the common local standard. International numbers should be preceded by a plus symbol.

properties.name: Ownership
properties.description: A text description of the manner in which title to a property is held (e.g., Trust, Corporation, Joint Tenant, Individual).

properties.name: OwnershipType
properties.description: The current type of ownership of the business being sold (e.g., Corporation, LLC, Sole Proprietor, Partnership).

properties.name: ParcelNumber
properties.description: A number used to uniquely identify a parcel or lot. This number is typically issued by the county or county assessor. The assessor's parcel number (APN) format varies from county to county. It is recommended that all parcel numbers are transmitted without dashes or hyphens.

properties.name: ParkingFeatures
properties.description: A list of features about or a description of the parking included in the sale/lease.

properties.name: ParkingTotal
properties.description: The total number of parking spaces included in the sale.

properties.name: ParkManagerName
properties.description: The name of the manager of the mobile home park.

properties.name: ParkManagerPhone
properties.description: North American 10-digit phone numbers should be in the format of ###-###-#### (separated by hyphens). Other conventions should use the common local standard. International numbers should be preceded by a plus symbol.
properties.displayNameFr: Numéro de téléphone du gestionnaire du parc

properties.name: ParkName
properties.description: The name of the mobile home park or corporate/commercial park.

properties.name: PastureArea
properties.description: A measurement or percentage of the property that has been allocated as pasture or grazing area.

properties.name: PatioAndPorchFeatures
properties.description: A list of features about or a description of the patio or porch included in the sale/lease.

properties.name: PendingTimestamp
properties.description: The transactional timestamp automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the most recent date/time the listing's status was set to Pending.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date où le statut En attente a été sélectionné

properties.name: PestControlExpense
properties.description: The annual expense that is not paid directly by the tenant and is included in the Operating Expense calculations.
properties.displayNameFr: Dépenses relatives à la lutte antiparasitaire

properties.name: PetsAllowed
properties.description: Indicates whether or not pets are allowed at the property being leased, usually as a list of yes, no and more detailed restrictions/allowances.

properties.name: PhotosChangeTimestamp
properties.description: A system-generated timestamp of when the last update or change to the photos for this listing was made.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date de la mise à jour des photos
properties.displayNameEs: Marca de Tiempo Cambio de Fotografías

properties.name: PhotosCount
properties.description: The total number of pictures or photos included with the listing.

properties.name: PoolExpense
properties.description: The annual expense that is not paid directly by the tenant and is included in the Operating Expense calculations.

properties.name: PoolFeatures
properties.description: A list of features about or a description of a pool included in the sale/lease.

properties.name: PoolPrivateYN
properties.description: The property has a privately owned pool that is included in the sale/lease.

properties.name: Possession
properties.description: A list defining when possession will occur (i.e., COE, COE+1, etc.).

properties.name: PossibleUse
properties.description: A list of the type(s) of possible or best uses of the property. Probable use gives a good indication of what the best use or potential use of the property could be (e.g., Residential, Recreational, Commercial, Retail).

properties.name: PostalCity
properties.description: The official city per the U.S. Postal Service (USPS), which may be different from the recorded city.

properties.name: PostalCode
properties.description: The postal code portion of a street or mailing address.

properties.name: PostalCodePlus4
properties.description: The last four digits of a nine-digit U.S. ZIP Code.

properties.name: PowerProduction
properties.description: A collection of the types of power production system(s) available on the property. The collection includes the type of system and other details about the power produced and age of the system.

properties.name: PowerProductionType
properties.description: A list of the types of power production systems available on the property. The key characteristics of the system are expected to appear as the type in related power production fields in a flattened implementation (RETS 1.x only). A relational implementation of power production must omit the type from the field name and use PowerProductionType to create a vertical representation of the various types of power production available. Note that PV Solar is the only type of power production currently justified in multiple markets. Renewables that could be added in the future depending on uptake include Wind, Geothermal and Thin Film Solar.

properties.name: PowerProductionYN
properties.description: A flag indicating that the listing has a Power Production system.

properties.name: PreviousListPrice
properties.description: The most recent previous list price of the listing.

properties.name: PriceChangeTimestamp
properties.description: The transactional timestamp automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the date/time the listing's price was last changed.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date de la mise à jour du prix de l’inscription
properties.displayNameEs: Marca de Tiempo Cambio de Precio

properties.name: PrivateOfficeRemarks
properties.description: A Remarks field that is only visible to members of the same offices as the listing agent.

properties.name: PrivateRemarks
properties.description: Remarks that may contain security or proprietary information and should be restricted from public view.

properties.name: ProfessionalManagementExpense
properties.description: The annual expense that is not paid directly by the tenant and is included in the Operating Expense calculations. This is for a management company. Use ManagerExpense for a individual manager.

properties.name: PropertyAttachedYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not the primary structure is attached to another structure that is not included in the sale (i.e., one unit of a duplex). This flag may be True/False, Yes/No or a list of attached or detached. As with all flags, the field may be null. In some systems, this information may be part of the property subtype.

properties.name: PropertyCondition
properties.description: A list describing the condition of the property and any structures included in the sale.

properties.name: PropertySubType
properties.description: A list of types of residential and residential lease properties (e.g., Single-Family Residence, Condominium, Townhouse) or a list of subtypes for mobile (e.g., Manufactured Home, Manufactured On Land).

properties.name: PropertyTimeZoneName
properties.description: The standard name of the property time zone, as provided by the IANA tz database.

properties.name: PropertyTimeZoneObservesDstYN
properties.displayName: Property Time Zone Observes DST Yes/No
properties.description: Indicates whether the property is in a time zone that observes Daylight Savings Time (DST).

properties.name: PropertyTimeZoneStandardOffset
properties.description: The time zone offset is the difference, in minutes, between Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) and local time.

properties.name: PropertyType
properties.description: A list of types of properties (e.g., Residential, Lease, Income, Land, Mobile, Commercial Sale).

properties.name: PublicRemarks
properties.description: Text remarks that may be displayed to the public. In an MLS, it is the field where information is entered for the public. This information is intended to be visible online. This is typically information that describes the selling points of the building and/or land for sale. Local conditions and rules will determine what such content can contain. Generally, any information pertaining to entry to the property, the seller and/or tenant, or listing member contact information is excluded. In other systems, these remarks will be determined by local business rules.

properties.name: PublicSurveyRange
properties.description: The range identified by the Public Land Survey System (PLSS).
properties.displayNameFr: Rangée selon le Public Land Survey System

properties.name: PublicSurveySection
properties.description: The section identified by the Public Land Survey System (PLSS).
properties.displayNameFr: Section selon le Public Land Survey System

properties.name: PublicSurveyTownship
properties.description: The township identified by the Public Land Survey System (PLSS).
properties.displayNameFr: Comté selon le Public Land Survey System

properties.name: PurchaseContractDate
properties.description: With for-sale listings, this represents the date an offer was accepted and the listing was no longer on market. This is the date entered by the agent reflecting when the change occurred contractually, not a timestamp of when the change was made in the MLS. With lease listings, this may represent a meeting of the minds to lease but with some contractual requirements yet to be fulfilled, such as contract signing or receipt of the deposit.

properties.name: RangeArea
properties.description: The measurement or percentage of the property that has been allocated as range.

properties.name: RentControlYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not the property is in a rent-control area.

properties.name: RentIncludes
properties.description: A list of services or items that the tenant is not responsible to pay.

properties.name: RoadFrontageType
properties.description: A pick list of types of road frontage (i.e., County, Freeway, Interstate, None). The road frontage of the property is an important factor in determining property value and its appropriateness for intended use.
properties.displayNameFr: Type de façade de la route

properties.name: RoadResponsibility
properties.description: The person or entity responsible for road maintenance (e.g., City, County, Private).
properties.displayNameFr: Responsable de l’entretien de la route

properties.name: RoadSurfaceType
properties.description: A pick list of types of road surfaces in use to access the property. Road surfaces for property access are an important factor in determining property value and its appropriateness for intended use.
properties.displayNameFr: Type de surface de la route

properties.name: Roof
properties.description: A list describing the roof style type (e.g., Spanish Tile, Composite, Shake).

properties.name: Rooms
properties.description: A collection of types of rooms and details/features about the given room.

properties.name: RoomsTotal
properties.description: The number of rooms in a dwelling.

properties.name: RoomType
properties.description: A list of the types used in room repeating elements. The type is a list of possible room types (i.e., bedroom, bathroom, living room, workshop, etc.). Each selected is expected to appear as the type in the related room fields in a flattened implementation (RETS 1.x only). A relational implementation of rooms must omit the type from the field name and use RoomType to create a vertical representation of the various rooms. Note that garage or basement should not be added as a room type, as these are represented by the ParkingFeatures and Basement fields, respectively.

properties.name: RVParkingDimensions
properties.description: The dimensions of the RV parking area minimally represented as length and width (i.e., 25' x 18') or a measurement of all sides of the polygon representing the usable RV parking space (i.e., 33' x 15' x 12' x 60').
properties.displayNameFr: Dimensions de l’espace de stationnement pour VR
properties.displayNameEs: Dimensiones de Estacionamiento de Vehículo Recreativo

properties.name: SeatingCapacity
properties.description: The seating capacity of the business being sold.

properties.name: SecurityFeatures
properties.description: A list describing the security features included in the sale/lease.

properties.name: SeniorCommunityYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not a community is a senior community.

properties.name: SerialU
properties.description: The serial number of the mobile or manufactured home. For the first or only unit/section, use Serial U over Serial X or Serial XX.

properties.name: SerialX
properties.description: The serial number of the mobile or manufactured home. For two units/sections, Serial U should be used first, Serial X second.

properties.name: SerialXX
properties.description: The serial number of the mobile or manufactured home. For two units/sections, Serial U should be used first, Serial X (or Serial XX) second.

properties.name: Sewer
properties.description: A list describing the sewer or septic features of a property.

properties.name: ShowingAdvanceNotice
properties.description: The hours of advance notice required to schedule a showing.

properties.name: ShowingAttendedYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not this home requires an attended showing (i.e., Yes = licensed agent representing the seller must be present during showing).

properties.name: ShowingConsiderations
properties.description: A pick list of conditions that may require caution or further consideration, such as bringing someone with you, when showing the property (i.e., Electricity Not On, Inconsistent Cell Service, No Exterior Lighting).

properties.name: ShowingContactName
properties.description: The name of the contact for the showing of the listed property.
properties.displayNameFr: Nom du contact pour la visite

properties.name: ShowingContactPhone
properties.description: A telephone number that should be called to arrange showing the property.
properties.displayNameFr: Numéro de téléphone du contact pour la visite

properties.name: ShowingContactPhoneExt
properties.description: The extension of the given phone number, if applicable.
properties.displayNameFr: Poste téléphonique du contact pour la visite

properties.name: ShowingContactType
properties.description: The type of contact for the showing (i.e., Agent, Broker, Seller).
properties.displayNameFr: Type de contact pour la visite

properties.name: ShowingDays
properties.description: The days of the week that the property is available for showing (i.e., Sundays, Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays, Fridays, Saturdays).

properties.name: ShowingEndTime
properties.description: From the days selected in the ShowingDays field, the end time that the property is available for showing.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure de fin de la visite

properties.name: ShowingInstructions
properties.description: Remarks that detail the seller's instructions for showing the subject property. Showing instructions may include contact information, showing times, notice required or other information. These remarks are privileged and are not for public viewing.

properties.name: ShowingRequirements
properties.description: A pick list of types of notice required to see the home (i.e., Appointment Required, Courtesy Call Only, Go Direct, etc.).

properties.name: ShowingServiceName
properties.description: The name of the showing service used to request showings on the listing.

properties.name: ShowingStartTime
properties.description: From the days selected in the ShowingDays field, the start time that the property is available for showing.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure de début de la visite

properties.name: SignOnPropertyYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not there a sign on the property.

properties.name: SimpleDaysOnMarket
properties.description: A simplified version of days on market (DOM) where the calculation is a simple start and end, such as the difference between the listing input or contract date and the date of sale.

properties.name: Skirt
properties.description: A list of types of mobile home skirting.

properties.name: SocialMedia
properties.description: A collection of social media items related to the Property record.

properties.name: SourceSystem
properties.description: The source system of the Property record.

properties.name: SourceSystemID
properties.description: The OUID Resource's OrganizationUniqueId of the source record provider. The source system is the system from which the record was directly received. In cases where the source system was not where the record originated (the authoritative system), see the Originating System fields.

properties.name: SourceSystemKey
properties.description: The system key, a unique record identifier, from the source system. The source system is the system from which the record was directly received. In cases where the source system was not where the record originated (the authoritative system), see the Originating System fields.

properties.name: SourceSystemName
properties.description: The name of the immediate record provider. The system from which the record was directly received. The legal name of the company.

properties.name: SpaFeatures
properties.description: A list of features or a description of the spa included in the sale/lease.

properties.name: SpaYN
properties.description: Indicates whether or not the property has a spa.

properties.name: SpecialLicenses
properties.description: Special licenses required/used by the business being sold (e.g., Beer/Wine, Class H, Professional, Gambling, None).

properties.name: SpecialListingConditions
properties.description: A list of options that describe the type of sale (e.g., Standard, REO, Short Sale, Probate, Auction, NOD) at the time of listing.

properties.name: StandardStatus
properties.description: The status of the listing as it reflects the state of the contract between the listing agent and seller, or an agreement with a buyer (e.g., Active, Active Under Contract, Canceled, Closed, Expired, Pending, Withdrawn). This is a single-select field.

properties.name: StartShowingDate
properties.description: The date the listing agent/broker expects to start showing the property.

properties.name: StateOrProvince
properties.description: Text field containing the accepted postal abbreviation for the state or province.

properties.name: StateRegion
properties.description: A subsection or area of a defined state or province (e.g., Florida Keys, Hudson Valley in New York, Silicon Valley in California).

properties.name: StatusChangeTimestamp
properties.description: The transactional timestamp automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the date/time the listing's status was last changed.
properties.displayNameFr: Heure et date de la mise à jour du statut
properties.displayNameEs: Marca de Tiempo Cambio de Estado

properties.name: Stories
properties.description: The number of floors in the property being sold.

properties.name: StoriesTotal
properties.description: The total number of floors in the building. In the case of multi-dwelling structures, this is the entire structure and not the individual dwelling being sold.

properties.name: StreetAdditionalInfo
properties.description: Information other than a prefix or suffix for the street portion of a postal address.

properties.name: StreetDirPrefix
properties.description: The direction indicator that precedes the listed property's street name.

properties.name: StreetDirSuffix
properties.description: The direction indicator that follows a listed property's street address.

properties.name: StreetName
properties.description: The street name portion of a listed property's street address.

properties.name: StreetNumber
properties.description: The street number portion of a listed property's street address. In some areas, the street number may contain nonnumerical characters. This field can also contain extensions and modifiers to the street number, such as "1/2" or "B." This street number field should not include prefixes, direction or suffixes.

properties.name: StreetNumberNumeric
properties.description: The integer portion of the street number.
properties.displayNameFr: Numéro de la rue en chiffres

properties.name: StreetSuffix
properties.description: The suffix portion of a listed property's street address.

properties.name: StreetSuffixModifier
properties.description: Allows for the entry of a unique street suffix that was not found in the Street Suffix pick list or to extend or prefix the suffix.

properties.name: StructureType
properties.description: The type of structure that the property completely or partially encompasses. For example, houses or cabins are the overall structure and typically sold or leased as a whole. Multifamily and docks may be sold in whole but are often sold or leased by unit/slip. This field is the type of structure as opposed to style, which is under the Architectural Style field.

properties.name: SubAgencyCompensation
properties.description: The total commission to be paid to the subagency, expressed as either a percentage or a constant currency amount.

properties.name: SubAgencyCompensationType
properties.description: A list of types to clarify the value entered in the SubAgencyCompensation field. For example $, % or some other clarification of SubAgencyCompensation.
properties.displayNameFr: Type de rémunération de l’agence secondaire

properties.name: SubdivisionName
properties.description: A neighborhood, community, complex or builder tract.

properties.name: SuppliesExpense
properties.description: The annual expense that is not paid directly by the tenant and is included in the Operating Expense calculations.

properties.name: SyndicateTo
properties.description: When permitted by the broker, the options made by the agent on behalf of the seller, where they would like their listings syndicated (e.g., Zillow, Trulia, Realtor.com, Homes.com).

properties.name: SyndicationRemarks
properties.description: For MLSs that host a separate "Public Remarks" for syndication purposes, this field should be defaulted to contain public remarks. Upon broker decision, it should be modified to include contact and other information denied by IDX rules but allowed under local and national regulations.

properties.name: TaxAnnualAmount
properties.description: The annual property tax amount as of the last assessment made by the taxing authority.

properties.name: TaxAnnualAmountPerLivingAreaUnit
properties.displayName: Tax Annual Amount Per Living Area Unit
properties.description: The annual property tax amount as of the last assessment made by the taxing authority divided by the property’s living area. The LivingAreaUnits field defines the area unit type (e.g., Square Feet or Square Meters).

properties.name: TaxAnnualAmountPerSquareFoot
properties.displayName: Tax Annual Amount Per Square Foot
properties.description: The annual property tax amount as of the last assessment made by the taxing authority divided by the property’s living area square footage.

properties.name: TaxAssessedValue
properties.description: The property value as of the last assessment made by the taxing authority.

properties.name: TaxBlock
properties.description: A type of legal description for land in developed areas where streets or other rights-of-ways delineate large parcels of land referred to as divided into lots on which homes or other types of developments are built. An example would read "Lot 12 of Block 45 of Tract 3002 of the City of San Dunes, Desert County." Such a description would also reference an official plat filed with the clerk or recorder for that area which shows the location of the block and often the dimensions of the lots therein.

properties.name: TaxBookNumber

The Home Energy Rating System (HERS) Index is most common with new homes and runs with a lower number being more efficient. A net-zero home uses zero energy and has a HERS score of 0. When ratings are involved, it is not uncommon for the final rating to be either higher or lower than the target preliminary rating. Sometimes the final approval is not available until after sale and occupancy. Status indicates what the target was at the time of listing and may be updated when verification is complete. To limit liability concerns, this field reflects information that was available at the time of listing or updated later and should be confirmed by the buyer.

properties.name: PowerProductionAnnual
properties.description: The most important metric of a renewables system is the amount of power it produces per year. This number can be actual or estimated. Annual production for systems producing electricity like wind or solar are measured in kilowatt hours (kWh) per year. A kWh is like a measure of the distance traveled per hour for a car - how far did it go over a certain period of time. Annual production is influenced by the size of the system, the conditions (How shady are the trees? How many cloudy days?) and the installation. Sellers typically have access to software that provides historical production totals.

properties.name: PowerProductionAnnualStatus
properties.description: The most important metric of a renewables system is the amount of power it produces per year. This number can be actual, estimated or a combination of each if less than 12 months of actual data is available (any missing months of actual data is extrapolated). This field allows the status of the number shown in the PowerProducationAnnual field to be clarified.
properties.displayNameEs: Estado de Producción de Energía Anual

properties.name: PowerProductionSize
properties.description: The "capacity" of a renewables system. Size is measured in kilowatts (kW) DC (direct current). A kW indicates how much power the system can produce under standard conditions, like the size of a car engine. Renewables systems are sized when they are installed to cover all or a portion of the power needs of the property. Therefore, a system designed to produce 50% of the power needs will be sized smaller than a system on the exact same property designed to produce 100%. Size may be influenced by available space at the property, orientation, landscaping, etc.

properties.name: PowerProductionYearInstall
properties.description: The year a renewables system was installed. Ideally, this should be the year the system was interconnected with the grid and began producing power. Renewables systems have a limited lifespan, and recording the year a system was installed helps buyers and appraisers determine the remaining useful life of the system.
properties.displayNameEs: Instalación Anual de Producción de Energía
